worksheet.commonFeedback:
Using MATLAB

 

function dy=prob2416sys(x,y,E,I,w,L)
dy=[y(2);(w*L*x/2-w*x^2/2)/(E*I)];

 

clear,clc,clf
E = 200;I =30000;w= 15;L = 3;
xspan=[0:L/5:L];bc=[0 0];
[x,T]=bvshoot(@prob2416sys,xspan,bc,E,I,w,L)     

function [x,y]=bvshoot(func,tspan,bc,varargin)
% bvshoot: shooting method boundary value ODEs
%   [x,y]=bvshoot(func,tspan,bc,tout,p1,p2,...):
%      uses the shooting method to solve a linear 2nd-order ODE
% input:
%   func = name of the M-file that evaluates the ODEs
%   tspan = [ti , tf]; initial and final times
%   bc = boundary values of Dirichlet conditions
%   tout = desired times for output
%   p1,p2,... = additional parameters used by func
% output:
%   x = vector of independent variable
%   y = vector of solution for dependent variables
 
%Shooting method
%first shot
za1=1;ya=bc(:,1);yb=bc(:,2);
[x1,y1]=ode45(func,tspan,[ya za1],[],varargin{:});
yb1=y1(length(y1));
%second shot
za2=za1*1.1;
[x2,y2]=ode45(func,tspan,[ya za2],[],varargin{:});
yb2=y2(length(y2));
%final shot
za=za1+(za2-za1)/(yb2-yb1)*(yb-yb1);
[x,y]=ode45(func,tspan,[ya za],[],varargin{:});
 
% analytical solution
E = 200;I =30000;w= 15;L = 3;
tanal=[0:L/100:L];
yanal=w*L*tanal.^3./(12*E*I)-w*tanal.^4/(24*E*I)-w*L^3*tanal/(24*E*I);
subplot(2,1,1)
plot(x,y(:,1),tanal,yanal)
grid;legend('shooting','analytical')
ylabel('y (m)')
subplot(2,1,2)
plot(x,y(:,2))
xlabel('x (m)'),ylabel('dy/dx (m/m)')
 
disp('results:')    
fprintf('Final shot: za = %8.4g   y = %8.4g\n',za,y(length(y)))
fprintf('\n     x            y         dy/dx\n')
disp([x y])

          0.6   -1.566e-06  -2.2275e-06
          1.2   -2.511e-06   -8.325e-07
          1.8   -2.511e-06    8.325e-07
